CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 4, 1954, pg. 1 reads: "4th Prize - Bonnie Lynn Dickinson, 18 pounds, 25 1/2 inches tall, 9 months old, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Ralph Dickinson, 19 Farragut Street, Uniontown, reaches for he fourth prize $25 check which she won."
TitMainTitle: John Ruffing Jr. presenting fourth prize to Bonnie Lynn Dickinson, daughter of Mrs. Ralph Dickinson, in Centre Avenue YMCA during Carnation Milk baby contest
